original: Lindstedt, Martin Albert, fil. mag., läroverksadjunkt, Kalmar, f. 9/9/93 i Kristianopel, Blek. L, av J. E. L. o. Karolina Jonasson. G. 24 m. Mary Wikström. Barn: Gunnar f. 27, jur, stud., Lund, Erik 29, med. stud., Lund, Göran 37. — Stud:ex. i Lund 10, fil. mag. 15, efterpr. 18, provår v. Upps. h. a. 1. 28. Res. t. Tyskl. 12, 19 o. 23. E. lär. i Piteå 19-23, lär. v. Bollnäs ensk. mellansk. 23-25, vik. ämneslär. i Boillnäs 26, ord. där s. å., adj. i Falköp. 29, adj. i modersm. o. hist. m. samh :(lära v. Kalmar h. a. 1. sed. 34.
translated: Lindstedt, Martin Albert, Master of Philosophy, high school teacher, Kalmar, born on September 9, 1893 in Kristianopel, Blekinge County, son of J. E. L. and Karolina Jonasson. Married on the 24th with Mary Wikström. Children: Gunnar, born in 1927, studying law in Lund, Erik, born in 1929, studying medicine in Lund, Göran, born in 1937. Martin underwent his studies: matriculated in Lund in 1910, obtained his Master of Philosophy in 1915, re-examined in 1918, one-year probationary period at Uppsala University in 1928. Resided in Germany in 1912, 1919, and 1923. He worked as a teacher in Piteå from 1919 to 1923, as a teacher at Bollnäs private middle school from 1923 to 1925, temporary subject teacher in Bollnäs in 1926, regular teacher there in the same year. He became a high school teacher in Falköping in 1929, teaching mother tongue and history with social studies in Kalmar since 1934.
